Bringing up Hiroshima was inevitable.<br>
<br>
The decisions were made and the bomb was dropped.  In hindsight it was one of the worst atrocities attributed to the war.  At the time it felt like a necessary and justifiable evil.<br>
<br>
Remember after all was said and done the bomb was a large part of what ended the war (on both sides of the world).  It's sad, but true.<br>
<br>
200, 000 thousand civilians died in that blast.<br>
Countless other deaths were prevented (around the world).<br>
A new age of warfare began.<br>
<br>
Separating "military lives" and "civilian lives" is largely a modern way of thinking.  Throughout history winning a war often meant decimating a people.<br>
<br>
