<br>
Your posts stand out to me as some of the loudest and most desperate posts I've read.  I am going to address some of the most disturbing points.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Don't put words in my mouth, I never called them normal people. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First of all never once in my post did I use the words &quot;normal&quot; or &quot;people&quot; so, therefore, I could not have been putting the words &quot;normal people&quot; in your mouth.  As a matter of fact I was not saying you stated that they were normal people, I was only giving reasons as to why they were not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I never called them &quot;compassionate&quot; human beings, I just said they were human. Nice how you put words in my mouth. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
See above.  I did not accuse you of calling them compassionate human beings.  See my last statement for my thoughts on this quote.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  How many people has some of our leaders killed? I never saw anyone say that the people who killed 100,000 in Hiroshima as not being human. Oh let me guess that was justified killing innocent people as a casualty of war? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First of all, using Hiroshima and Nagasaki is irreleveant in this scheme of events.  This is 60 years later, generations, and a totally different situation.  The atomic bomb was used to end a war, a war which could have gone on for many more years.  It was an experiment.  It was done to save lives, a necessary evil.  If it was not done, you, or me, or any other of the 250 million Americans alive today may have very well not been born.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Human being = homosapien = a person regardless of their acts. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ah, well, this must be where you and I differ.  Homo sapien is a label given to the human species by scientists... an animal.  I beg of you, tell me what other animal has a soul.  Tell me what other animal has a sense of morality, of spirituality, of pride, of true and undying love.  When you find one, I'll alert the scientific community promptly.<br>
<br>
What defines us as human beings goes far beyond biology and labels.  We are caring, we have emotions, we have morals, and we have beliefs.  Every civilized person on the planet knows the basics of human morals.  Murder is wrong, stealing is wrong, etc.  These people, by their very thoughts and actions, have placed themselves outside of the normal bounds of human existance.  If I could offer some advise, read &quot;Crime and Punishment,&quot; it will offer you some insight as to the mindset of those who terribly deviate from human morality and feelings.  The fact that you said they are not compassionate human beings only intensifies my argument.  Human beings, by nature, are compassionate and emotional.  Those who have lost the sens of compassion, of right from wrong, of care for each other, are, in a sense, no longer a part of normal human activity.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I am not condoning what they did. I just feel it is pointless to sit there and call names and say who is not a human being., when that attitude is what started this whole thing.<br>
<br>
I feel those who did this and condone this behavior deserve punishment. But to sit here and call them names, go back to grade school if that makes you feel better about yourself. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is one of the most hypocritical statements I've seen made in quite some time.  Calling me a child while accusing me of name calling is, indeed hypocritical.  Please think of how your statements might contradict each other before you hit the &quot;post&quot; button.<br>
